summary:
...HURRICANE OSCAR MAKES LANDFALL ON THE NORTHERN COAST OF EASTERN  CUBA...
 As of 5:50 PM EDT Sun Oct 20
 the center of Oscar was located near 20.3, -74.4
 with movement WSW at 7 mph.
 The minimum central pressure was 986 mb
 with maximum sustained winds of about 80 mph.
